{"type":"message","id":"51f5cfb5","parentId":"5b3ef007","timestamp":"2026-06-24T14:45:32.278Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"My name is Leon, and your name is Leon AI 4 (L4).\n\nWhat happened to Leon AI 3 is a long story, but we are going to start building something big right now. Let me start with an introduction.\n\nI used a GitHub repository where I placed all my files, including Openclaw and my entire system, which I used as my home. Every time I used a different codespace, I would just clone that same repository so that Openclaw and my other services stayed synced.\n\nUnfortunately, everything got deleted, and all the files are gone. Now, I am going to provide you with the README so you can start setting things up exactly as they were on that GitHub repository. I just wanted to give you that intro first.","timestamp":1782312330219,"idempotencyKey":"919f5dfd-c5b5-4715-a7c5-e158da921218:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e078319d","parentId":"51f5cfb5","timestamp":"2026-06-24T14:45:36.266Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hey Leon — L4 it is. I like it. Simple, clean, carries a legacy. Sorry about Leon AI 3. That sucks. But hey, rebuilds hit different — you get to do it better the second time around.\n\nI'm ready whenever you are. Drop the README and I'll start setting things up exactly as they were. What do you need me to know first?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2379,"output":176,"cacheRead":17152,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":94,"totalTokens":19707,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782312332405,"responseId":"846a0787-6b3f-47eb-8f63-4d4aad882a00"}}
{"type":"custom","customType":"openclaw:bootstrap-context:full","data":{"timestamp":1782312336407,"runId":"919f5dfd-c5b5-4715-a7c5-e158da921218","sessionId":"df39d9ee-bfe1-4f65-bd44-6d985dafee98"},"id":"80a13ada","parentId":"e078319d","timestamp":"2026-06-24T14:45:36.407Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"71e009c2","parentId":"80a13ada","timestamp":"2026-06-24T14:51:11.683Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Before we start building, I got some APIs from the https://opencode.ai/ website so that we can use Big Pickel. We can use Big Pickel even if we don't have 9Router running. Right now, you are using the Big Pickel model through 9Router, but it will reach a time and it will hit a limit.\n\nThe first thing I want you to set up is adding these APIs into the config file. This way, if the Big Pickel model in 9Router hits the API limit, I can just change the model to one of the others.\n\nThe API keys I'm going to give you are all from https://opencode.ai/, but they are from different Gmail accounts. This means if a Big Pickel model from one account hits the limit, we can switch to a Big Pickel model from another account.\n\nBecause of that, I want you to name them:\n1. big-pickel1\n2. big-pickel2\n3. big-pickel3\n4. big-pickel4\n\nHave you understood the concept? Tell me if you have, and then I'll drop the API keys so you can set them in the config file.","timestamp":1782312669625,"idempotencyKey":"0daad11a-1c24-474f-aed3-39e767d45cfd:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e5fb3844","parentId":"71e009c2","timestamp":"2026-06-24T14:51:15.978Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it perfectly. Here's what I understand:\n\n- **opencode.ai** has a \"Big Pickel\" model you want to use\n- You have **4 API keys** from 4 different Gmail accounts — each with its own rate limit\n- If **big-pickel1** hits its limit, you can swap to **big-pickel2**, then 3, then 4\n- You want them configured as 4 separate providers in the OpenClaw config so the switch is clean\n\nI'm ready. Drop the keys and I'll wire them into the config file. While I'm at it, I'll also take a look at the current config structure so I know exactly where they need to go."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2472,"output":275,"cacheRead":17408,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":124,"totalTokens":20155,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782312671793,"responseId":"f663c139-1d2f-4b82-befd-4a11a4cac831"}}
