{"type":"message","id":"dbfe8694","parentId":"fe9dc95a","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:36:51.224Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"As you know, with the codespace, you can't be available 24/7 because the codespace gets stopped sometimes. That's why we have to push our updates to the repository.\n\nWhat I want is for you to set up two commands: the setup command and the start command.\n\n1. The setup command\n   This should work if I move to a new codespace. If I have cloned this repository and I move to a new codespace, running that command should install everything and all our information to that codespace.\n\n2. The start script\n   This is for when I stop a codespace and restart it after some time (like at night). I need to run the start command to start all our environment services:\n   (a) The Tailscale service\n   (b) The 9-router service\n   (c) The Openclaw gateway\n\nTo further simplify this, let me send you the README of how the setup was before the files got deleted so that you understand it. Other things like the Remote Browser and the Money Printer, we shall add those later.\n\nI want to go take a shower right now, so please focus on setting up these commands first: the setup command for a new codespace, and the start command if I'm restarting on the same codespace. \n\nhttps://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3/blob/openclaw/README.md. That is the link to the README. It is on that same repository. Since you already have the token for my GitHub account, you can check that same repository but on a different branch. \n\nThe branch is called openclaw. That was the branch where the environment was set before files got deleted. As you can see from the files there now, I want to start fresh on this main branch. \n\nIf you go to that openclaw branch and look into the README (which wasn't deleted), you will understand the setup and how everything was.","timestamp":1782315409255,"idempotencyKey":"9c3e0532-9a76-4534-9875-8ff2ff9e3f9d:user"}}
