{"type":"message","id":"76d8fe49","parentId":"9c6bdb69","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:38:59.975Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_1urH2UUgXBWExGOx1t5i6512","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🐾 Claw Pack — Portable OpenClaw Environment\n\n> Your entire AI environment: OpenClaw agent, 9-router, Tailscale, and remote browser.\n> **Codespaces are temporary houses. The `openclaw` branch is the family you carry.**\n\n---\n\n## 🏠 The Philosophy\n\nThink of each Codespace as a house you settle into for a while. You'll eventually move to a new one. What travels with you is the **`openclaw` branch** — it contains:\n\n- 🖥️ **Remote browser** — all tabs, cookies, sessions, bookmarks, history, downloads\n- 🤖 **OpenClaw** — your AI agent, memory, conversations, identity\n- 🌐 **9-router** — 200+ AI models, config, auth keys\n- 🔗 **Tailscale** — network identity, mesh connections\n- 📝 **Workspace** — AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, MEMORY.md, daily notes, everything\n\n**Everything in the remote browser is tracked and pushed.** When you move houses (codespaces), you clone the `openclaw` branch and pick up exactly where you left off.\n\n---\n\n## 📦 Current Environment (2026-06-17)\n\n| Component | Version / Detail |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| **OS** | Ubuntu 24.04.4 LTS |\n| **Kernel** | 6.8.0-1052-azure |\n| **OpenClaw** | v2026.6.8 (844f405) |\n| **9-router** | v0.4.80 |\n| **Tailscale** | v1.98.4 |\n| **Docker Chrome** | Chromium in Docker (streaming 3001 / CDP 9223) |\n| **Git branch** | `openclaw` |\n| **GitHub** | `Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3` |\n| **Codespace** | `codespaces-ad62bd` |\n| **Disk** | 32G overlay, ~62% used |\n| **Pull config** | `pull.rebase = false` — clean pulls without stashing |\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start (Fresh Codespace)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Clone\ngit clone -b openclaw https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\ncd Codespace-3\n\n# 2. Setup (first time only — builds browser Docker image, restores state)\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh\n\n# 3. Start everything\n./start.sh\n\n# 4. Expose ports in Codespaces Ports panel:\n#    - 3001  → Browser streaming (login: leon / changeme)\n#    - 18789 → OpenClaw dashboard\n```\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ All Services\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Your Codespace                        │\n│                                                           │\n│   ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐   │\n│   │  Docker  │    │ OpenClaw │◄──►│   9-router       │   │\n│   │  Chrome  │    │:18789    │    │:20128 (200+ AI)│   │\n│   │:3001/9223│    └────┬─────┘    └────────┬─────────┘   │\n│   └────┬─────┘         │                    │             │\n│        │               ▼                    ▼             │\n│        │     ┌──────────────────────────────────┐        │\n│        └────►│          Tailscale               │        │\n│              │  100.84.138.107 (this machine)    │        │\n│              │  + 4 other nodes in mesh          │        │\n│              └──────────────────────────────────┘        │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Ports Summary\n\n| Port | Service | Access |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **3001** | Browser stream (web UI) | Codespaces Ports → HTTPS URL |\n| **9223** | Chrome DevTools Protocol | localhost only |\n| **18789** | OpenClaw dashboard | Codespaces Ports |\n| **20128** | 9-router API (OpenAI-compatible) | localhost or Tailscale |\n\n---\n\n## 📋 All Commands\n\n### Service lifecycle (run from workspace root)\n\n```bash\n./start.sh              # Start everything in order\n./stop.sh               # Stop all services\n./status.sh             # Check what's running\n./capture.sh            # Snapshot latest state before moving\n./setup.sh              # Full setup on a new Codespace\n```\n\n### Individual services\n\n```bash\n./bin/start-tailscale   # Install, start daemon, authenticate\n./bin/start-browser     # Start Docker Chrome (waits up to 120s for CDP)\n./bin/start-9router     # Start AI model router\n./bin/start-openclaw    # Start OpenClaw gateway\n```\n\n### CLI shortcuts (always available)\n\n```bash\nbrowser                 # Start/check Docker Chrome + show CDP info\ntiktok                  # Start TikTok bot (Zefoy) via browser CDP\nbetpawa                 # Start BetPawa Aviator + bot\nopenclaw-update         # Check/install newer OpenClaw version\n```\n\n### Git operations\n\n```bash\ngit pull origin openclaw     # Works cleanly (pull.rebase = false)\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"message\" && git push origin openclaw\n```\n\n### Browser CDP control\n\n```bash\nnode browser/browser.js status                     # List open tabs\nnode browser/browser.js open <url>                 # Open a new tab\nnode browser/browser.js eval <id> <code>           # Run JS in a tab\nnode browser/browser.js screenshot [id] [path]     # Capture a screenshot\nnode browser/browser.js navigate <id> <url>        # Navigate a tab\nnode browser/browser.js close <id>                 # Close a tab\n```\n\n### Keep-alive (prevents idle timeout)\n\n```bash\nbash bin/keepalive.sh &            # Start in background\nbash bin/keepalive.sh --stop       # Stop it\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Auto-Sync (Every 15 Minutes)\n\nThree cron jobs keep everything backed up automatically. All three are running and healthy.\n\n| Job | What it does | Status |\n|-----|-------------|--------|\n| **openclaw-sync-15min** | Commits workspace changes + pushes to `openclaw` branch | ✅ |\n| **session-auto-save-15min** | Saves conversation logs to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | ✅ |\n| **openclaw-auto-update** | Checks npm for newer OpenClaw version, auto-installs | ✅ |\n\n### What gets synced to the `openclaw` branch:\n\n- ✅ **Chrome browser profile** — ALL files in `browser/config/.config/chromium/`:\n  - Open tabs (via `--restore-last-session`)\n  - Cookies & login sessions (OneDrive, Discord, Telegram, etc.)\n  - Bookmarks, history, passwords\n  - Extension data (AdGuard, etc.)\n  - IndexedDB (WhatsApp, Telegram, Facebook, etc.)\n  - Local Storage, Service Workers\n  - Preferences, Secure Preferences\n- ✅ **OpenClaw memory database** (`config/openclaw/main.sqlite`)\n- ✅ **Session history** (chat logs)\n- ✅ **Workspace** (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, MEMORY.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md)\n- ✅ **Configuration** (OpenClaw, 9-router, Tailscale auth)\n- ✅ **System status** (`state/system-status.md`)\n\n> **The `browser/config/.config/chromium/` directory is NOT gitignored.** Every change in the browser is tracked and pushed. This is by design — portability is the priority.\n\n---\n\n## 🖥️ Remote Browser Details\n\nThe browser runs in Docker with its profile mounted from `browser/config/`. All Chrome runtime data persists in git.\n\n### Current open sessions (this codespace):\n- WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, TikTok, Facebook, YouTube, Twitch\n- OneDrive (logged in), Cloudflare Dashboard\n- Trivia Rumble (3 deployments: Vercel, Replit, Workers)\n- Google accounts, MyBookie, 123Movies\n- Multiple AdGuard tabs, chrome:// pages\n\n### Performance:\n- 15 FPS stream, 720p, software x264 (CRF 35)\n- Cache in RAM (`/dev/shm`) — saves disk, avoids tracking garbage\n- 2 GB shared memory\n- CDP timeout: 120 seconds (generous for first build)\n\n---\n\n## 🚚 Migrating to a New Codespace\n\n### Before leaving the old one:\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/codespace-*/Codespace-3   # or wherever you are\n./capture.sh                             # Snapshot latest state\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"pre-move capture $(date +%Y-%m-%d)\"\ngit push origin openclaw\n```\n\n### On the new Codespace:\n\n```bash\n# Clone the family — not just the code\ngit clone -b openclaw https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\ncd Codespace-3\n\n# First-time setup (builds Docker image, restores state)\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh\n\n# Start everything\n./start.sh\n\n# Expose ports in Codespaces panel:\n#   - 3001 → Browser stream\n#   - 18789 → OpenClaw dashboard\n```\n\n### What carries over:\n\n| Item | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| OpenClaw config, memory, sessions | ✅ Fully |\n| Agent identity & personality | ✅ Fully |\n| Chrome browser profile (tabs, cookies, logins, history) | ✅ Fully — all 329+ files tracked |\n| 9-router config & auth keys | ✅ Fully |\n| Tailscale identity & mesh | ✅ Re-auths automatically |\n| Keep-alive & auto-sync | ✅ Starts with `./start.sh` |\n| Open tabs restored | ✅ `--restore-last-session` flag |\n\n### What needs attention:\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Tailscale auth key | If expired, generate new one in Tailscale admin console |\n| Port exposure | Must re-expose 3001 & 18789 in new Codespace's Ports panel |\n| Docker image build | First `./start.sh` builds the Chromium image (~2 min) |\n\n---\n\n## 📁 Workspace File Structure\n\n```\n/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/        # The OpenClaw workspace\n├── README.md                   ← This file\n├── AGENTS.md                   ← Agent behavior guide\n├── SOUL.md                     ← Agent personality & tone\n├── MEMORY.md                   ← Long-term curated memory\n├── USER.md                     ← About you (Leon)\n├── TOOLS.md                    ← Tool config & local notes\n├── IDENTITY.md                 ← Agent identity (Leon AI 3)\n├── SERVICES.md                 ← Service command reference\n├── HEARTBEAT.md                ← Heartbeat checklists\n│\n├── sync.sh                     ← Auto-sync script\n├── setup.sh                    ← Full setup for new Codespace\n├── start.sh                    ← Start all services\n├── stop.sh                     ← Stop all services\n├── status.sh                   ← Health check\n├── capture.sh                  ← Snapshot before migration\n│\n├── memory/                     ← Daily session logs (YYYY-MM-DD.md)\n├── state/                      ← System status snapshots\n├── scripts/                    ← Utility scripts (session_saver.py, etc.)\n│\n├── claw-pack/                  ← Portable package (for export)\n├── codespace-export/           ← Bot suite (yt-bot branch)\n│\n├── .gitignore                  # NO exclusion for browser config\n└── .secure/                    ← Gitignored secrets (passwords, tokens)\n```\n\n**Note:** This is your workspace. It IS the `openclaw` branch of `Codespace-3`. When you clone, the workspace content comes with it.\n\n---\n\n## 📁 Bot Suite Companion\n\nThis package covers **AI infrastructure** (OpenClaw + 9-router + Tailscale + Remote Browser).\n\nFor the **bot suite** (TikTok bot, BetPawa bots), use the `yt-bot` branch:\n```\ngit clone -b yt-bot https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\n```\n\nTogether they form your complete Codespace environment.\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| `git pull` fails with \"unmerged files\" | `git stash` then pull — Chrome config changes are tracked now so this shouldn't happen |\n| `git pull` fails with \"cannot pull with rebase\" | `pull.rebase` is set to `false` — run `git config pull.rebase false` if it persists |\n| Browser stream blank | Expose **port 3001** in Codespaces Ports panel |\n| CDP timeout | `start-browser` now waits **120 seconds** — first build takes longest |\n| Browser sessions lost at new codespace | Push first: `git push origin openclaw` then re-clone |\n| Can't reach OpenClaw | Expose **port 18789** — test: `curl http://127.0.0.1:18789` |\n| 9-router offline | Test: `curl http://127.0.0.1:20128/v1/models` — reinstall: `npm install -g 9router@0.4.80` |\n| Tailscale won't connect | Run `./bin/start-tailscale` manually — might need new auth key |\n| Docker not available | Some Codespace repos don't have Docker enabled |\n| `openclaw: command not found` | Run: `export PATH=\"$PATH:$(npm config get prefix)/bin\"` then add to `~/.profile` |\n\n---\n\n## 🔒 Security Notes\n\n- Config files with secrets are in `.secure/` (gitignored)\n- Browser stream auth: **leon / changeme**\n- CDP port (9223) is localhost-only\n- Tailscale encrypts all traffic end-to-end\n- Chrome profile contains login sessions — these ARE synced to the branch (private repo)\n- GitHub token (`repo` scope) stored in `.secure/github-token.json` — expires 2026-09-13\n\n---\n\n## 📊 Current System State (2026-06-17 06:48 UTC)\n\n- **Uptime:** All services running\n- **Disk:** 32G overlay, 12G free (62% used)\n- **Memory:** ~62% used (typical)\n- **Tailscale:** Connected, 5 nodes in mesh\n- **Auto-sync:** All 3 cron jobs healthy, last runs OK\n- **Last push:** 60df6ef (06:40 UTC) — auto-sync"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782315539971}}
