{"type":"message","id":"a899eefd","parentId":"065b8823","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:40.310Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_01_ET_6zhhoNhjX7OEFY5gzMwW1929","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 2998 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":241,"aggregated":"6:  - You are validating channel, model, gateway, or tool config blocks\n46:- `agents.defaults.*` (workspace, model, thinking, heartbeat, memory, media, skills, sandbox)\n57:## Tools and custom providers\n59:Tool policy, experimental toggles, provider-backed tool config, and custom\n60:provider / base-URL setup moved to a dedicated page - see\n61:[Configuration - tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools).\n63:## Models\n65:Provider definitions, model allowlists, and custom provider setup live in\n66:[Configuration - tools and custom providers](/gateway/config-tools#custom-providers-and-base-urls).\n67:The `models` root also owns global model-catalog behavior.\n71:  models: {\n78:- `models.mode`: provider catalog behavior (`merge` or `replace`).\n79:- `models.providers`: custom provider map keyed by provider id.\n80:- `models.providers.*.localService`: optional on-demand process manager for\n81:  local model servers. OpenClaw probes the configured health endpoint, starts\n82:  the absolute `command` when needed, waits for readiness, then sends the model\n83:  request. See [Local model services](/gateway/local-model-services).\n84:- `models.pricing.enabled`: controls the background pricing bootstrap that\n87:  `models.providers.*.models[].cost` values still work for local cost estimates.\n104:        args: [\"-y\", \"@modelcontextprotocol/server-fetch\"],\n208:        apiKey: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"GEMINI_API_KEY\" }, // or plaintext string\n254:        config: { provider: \"twilio\" },\n268:- `plugins.entries.<id>.hooks.allowPromptInjection`: when `false`, core blocks `before_prompt_build` and ignores prompt-mutating fields from legacy `before_agent_start`, while preserving legacy `modelOverride` and `providerOverride`. Applies to native plugin hooks and supported bundle-provided hook directories.\n269:- `plugins.entries.<id>.hooks.allowConversationAccess`: when `true`, trusted non-bundled plugins may read raw conversation content from typed hooks such as `llm_input`, `llm_output`, `before_model_resolve`, `before_agent_reply`, `before_agent_run`, `before_agent_finalize`, and `agent_end`.\n270:- `plugins.entries.<id>.subagent.allowModelOverride`: explicitly trust this plugin to request per-run `provider` and `model` overrides for background subagent runs.\n271:- `plugins.entries.<id>.subagent.allowedModels`: optional allowlist of canonical `provider/model` targets for trusted subagent overrides. Use `\"*\"` only when you intentionally want to allow any model.\n272:- `plugins.entries.<id>.llm.allowModelOverride`: explicitly trust this plugin to request model overrides for `api.runtime.llm.complete`.\n273:- `plugins.entries.<id>.llm.allowedModels`: optional allowlist of canonical `provider/model` targets for trusted plugin LLM completion overrides. Use `\"*\"` only when you intentionally want to allow any model.\n283:surface and [Codex harness](/plugins/codex-harness) for the runtime model.\n286:It does not enable Codex plugins for OpenClaw provider runs, ACP","cwd":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782312873457}}
