{"type":"message","id":"e419149b","parentId":"17e24004","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:40.314Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's what I set up:\n\n**Config updated in** `/home/codespace/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:\n\n| Provider ID | API Key Source | Model | Base URL |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `big-pickel1` | Gmail account #1 | `big-pickle` | `https://opencode.ai/zen/v1` |\n| `big-pickel2` | Gmail account #2 | `big-pickle` | `https://opencode.ai/zen/v1` |\n\nBoth are OpenAI-compatible chat completions providers. The Gateway uses hot-reload by default, so the changes should be live already.\n\nTo use them, you'd reference them as:\n- `big-pickel1/big-pickle`\n- `big-pickel2/big-pickle`\n\nWhen 9Router hits its limit, you can just switch the primary model to one of these and keep going. Works great.\n\nWhen you get those keys from your other accounts, drop them in and I'll add **big-pickel3** and **big-pickel4** the same way. Ready when you are!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2277,"output":567,"cacheRead":43008,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":327,"totalTokens":45852,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782312961173,"responseId":"e4637d0a-71da-4060-a2ab-f54e47624b3b"}}
