{"type":"message","id":"9438c2f3","parentId":"bf6dc150","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:40.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pushed! ✅ \n\nHere's what I found and fixed:\n\n**The problem:** The `big-pickel1` and `big-pickel2` providers were defined in `models.providers` but weren't registered in `agents.defaults.models` — that's the agent's model registry that the Control UI uses for the model picker.\n\n**What I changed:**\n1. Added `models.mode: \"merge\"` to ensure custom providers merge properly with the catalog\n2. Registered both models in `agents.defaults.models`:\n   - `big-pickel1/big-pickle`\n   - `big-pickel2/big-pickle`\n3. Pushed the updates to the repo\n\nBoth API keys worked when I tested them directly against OpenCode Zen (200 OK response), so they're good. Try the Control UI now — you should see all three models in the picker:\n\n- `9router/oc/big-pickle` — via 9Router (default)\n- `big-pickel1/big-pickle` — via OpenCode Zen (account #1)\n- `big-pickel2/big-pickle` — via OpenCode Zen (account #2)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2207,"output":254,"cacheRead":79488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":81949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782314010236,"responseId":"b8daf485-39a7-45bf-9bf9-4ccbd961d823"}}
