{"type":"message","id":"fc5121ff","parentId":"6beee4ff","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:41.738Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh && \\\nsudo tailscaled --tun=userspace-networking &>/tmp/tailscaled.log & \\\nsudo tailscale up --auth-key=tskey-auth-kPjwrx2hmB21CNTRL-WtQZT8U4t5gB9PC9XTEm5gRAQ4xaHqhrK --ssh\n\nThe Tailscale authentication key is in there. Make sure you add it so it is configured into the system and I don't need to do it manually again; either on setup or start","timestamp":1782315758516,"idempotencyKey":"e7c12ce5-f86d-4534-be58-df53481db659:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"afc4dfc9","parentId":"fc5121ff","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:47.023Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Got it. Let me add that auth key to the start-tailscale script so it authenticates automatically every time."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_PcAzJVmczSlx50DhCxOF6955","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-tailscale"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-tailscale\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":53257,"output":154,"cacheRead":18048,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":73,"totalTokens":71459,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782315761859,"responseId":"d4d55d83-37b3-45ca-8a3e-994f8d21fc30"}}
{"type":"message","id":"80bf57f5","parentId":"afc4dfc9","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:47.406Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_PcAzJVmczSlx50DhCxOF6955","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\nset -euo pipefail\n\n# Start Tailscale - install if needed, start daemon, bring up connection\nSCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\necho \"🔗 Tailscale: checking...\"\n\n# Start tailscaled if not running\nif ! pgrep -x tailscaled >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Starting tailscaled...\"\n  sudo tailscaled --state=/var/lib/tailscale/tailscaled.state &>/dev/null &\n  sleep 2\nfi\n\n# Bring up tailscale\nif ! tailscale status --peers=false >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Authenticating Tailscale...\"\n  echo \"  ⚠️  You may need to authenticate at: https://login.tailscale.com\"\n  sudo tailscale up --accept-routes\nelse\n  echo \"  ✅ Tailscale is connected ($(tailscale status --peers=false | head -1 | awk '{print $1}'))\"\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1782315767404}}
{"type":"message","id":"75f89342","parentId":"80bf57f5","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:42:54.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_LNHQY4boNRiAEW3pxi9Y5390","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-tailscale","edits":[{"oldText":"SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\necho \"🔗 Tailscale: checking...\"\n\n# Start tailscaled if not running\nif ! pgrep -x tailscaled >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Starting tailscaled...\"\n  sudo tailscaled --state=/var/lib/tailscale/tailscaled.state &>/dev/null &\n  sleep 2\nfi\n\n# Bring up tailscale\nif ! tailscale status --peers=false >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Authenticating Tailscale...\"\n  echo \"  ⚠️  You may need to authenticate at: https://login.tailscale.com\"\n  sudo tailscale up --accept-routes\nelse\n  echo \"  ✅ Tailscale is connected ($(tailscale status --peers=false | head -1 | awk '{print $1}'))\"\nfi","newText":"SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/..\" && pwd)\"\nTAILSCALE_AUTH_KEY=\"tskey-…qhrK\"\necho \"🔗 Tailscale: checking...\"\n\n# Install Tailscale if not present\nif ! command -v tailscale &>/dev/null; then\n  echo \"  Installing Tailscale...\"\n  curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh\nfi\n\n# Start tailscaled if not running (use userspace networking for Codespaces)\nif ! pgrep -x tailscaled >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Starting tailscaled (userspace networking)...\"\n  sudo tailscaled --tun=userspace-networking --state=/var/lib/tailscale/tailscaled.state &>/tmp/tailscaled.log &\n  sleep 3\nfi\n\n# Bring up tailscale with auth key\nif ! tailscale status --peers=false >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n  echo \"  Authenticating Tailscale with auth key...\"\n  sudo tailscale up --auth-key=\"$TAILSCALE_AUTH_KEY\" --ssh --accept-routes\n  sleep 2\nfi\n\necho \"  ✅ Tailscale is connected ($(tailscale status --peers=false | head -1 | awk '{print $1}'))\""}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/bin/start-tailscale\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\":\"SCRIPT_DIR=\\\"$(cd \\\"$(dirname \\\"$0\\\")/..\\\" && pwd)\\\"\\necho \\\"🔗 Tailscale: checking...\\\"\\n\\n# Start tailscaled if not running\\nif ! pgrep -x tailscaled >/dev/null 2>&1; then\\n  echo \\\"  Starting tailscaled...\\\"\\n  sudo tailscaled --state=/var/lib/tailscale/tailscaled.state &>/dev/null &\\n  sleep 2\\nfi\\n\\n# Bring up tailscale\\nif ! tailscale status --peers=false >/dev/null 2>&1; then\\n  echo \\\"  Authenticating Tailscale...\\\"\\n  echo \\\"  ⚠️  You may need to authenticate at: https://login.tailscale.com\\\"\\n  sudo tailscale up --accept-routes\\nelse\\n  echo \\\"  ✅ Tailscale is connected ($(tailscale status --peers=false | head -1 | awk '{print $1}'))\\\"\\nfi\",\"newText\":\"SCRIPT_DIR=\\\"$(cd \\\"$(dirname \\\"$0\\\")/..\\\" && pwd)\\\"\\nTAILSCALE_AUTH_KEY=\\\"tskey-auth-kPjwrx2hmB21CNTRL-WtQZT8U4t5gB9PC9XTEm5gRAQ4xaHqhrK\\\"\\necho \\\"🔗 Tailscale: checking...\\\"\\n\\n# Install Tailscale if not present\\nif ! command -v tailscale &>/dev/null; then\\n  echo \\\"  Installing Tailscale...\\\"\\n  curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh\\nfi\\n\\n# Start tailscaled if not running (use userspace networking for Codespaces)\\nif ! pgrep -x tailscaled >/dev/null 2>&1; then\\n  echo \\\"  Starting tailscaled (userspace networking)...\\\"\\n  sudo tailscaled --tun=userspace-networking --state=/var/lib/tailscale/tailscaled.state &>/tmp/tailscaled.log &\\n  sleep 3\\nfi\\n\\n# Bring up tailscale with auth key\\nif ! tailscale status --peers=false >/dev/null 2>&1; then\\n  echo \\\"  Authenticating Tailscale with auth key...\\\"\\n  sudo tailscale up --auth-key=\\\"$TAILSCALE_AUTH_KEY\\\" --ssh --accept-routes\\n  sleep 2\\nfi\\n\\necho \\\"  ✅ Tailscale is connected ($(tailscale status --peers=false | head -1 | awk '{print $1}'))\\\"\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2323,"output":759,"cacheRead":69376,"