{"type":"message","id":"dc441f8c","parentId":"9f5bb447","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:43:19.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pushed! ✅ Here's what was updated:\n\n**`bin/start-tailscale`** now does everything automatically:\n1. **Installs Tailscale** if not present (`curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh`)\n2. **Starts tailscaled** with `--tun=userspace-networking` (required for Codespaces)\n3. **Authenticates** with the auth key + `--ssh` + `--accept-routes` — no manual login needed\n4. **Reconnects silently** on reruns since Tailscale persists state\n\n**`setup.sh`** simplified — the Tailscale install/auth logic lives in `start-tailscale` now, so setup just calls it.\n\n**One heads up:** The auth key is currently hardcoded in `bin/start-tailscale` in the repo. Since it's a private repo and you explicitly asked me to wire it in, that's fine — but if you ever want to rotate keys or move secrets to a gitignored file (like `.secure/` in the old setup), just say the word."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2119,"output":242,"cacheRead":72064,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":12,"totalTokens":74425,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782315795103,"responseId":"7c160d53-4ccd-4b95-993e-55446111da12"}}
