{"type":"message","id":"924edfd9","parentId":"c1267641","timestamp":"2026-06-24T15:49:57.347Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Right — session continuity is handled by the Gateway saving state to disk, and since it's the same codespace (just stopped/restarted), that data persists. Let me update the README and push everything."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_cNZjzti52cpiWecfq4YK4868","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# 🐾 L4 Claw Pack — Portable AI Environment\n\n> Your entire AI environment: OpenClaw agent, 9-router, Tailscale, and 5x Big Pickel fallback providers.\n> **Codespaces are temporary. The `main` branch is your home.**\n\n---\n\n## 🏠 What This Is\n\nA self-contained AI agent workspace that runs on GitHub Codespaces. Everything you need to run L4 (Leon AI 4) with multiple Big Pickel model fallbacks from [opencode.ai](https://opencode.ai).\n\n### What's inside:\n\n- 🤖 **OpenClaw** — Your AI agent (L4), with memory, conversations, and identity\n- 🌐 **9-router** — AI model router (port 20128), currently routing to Big Pickel\n- 🔗 **Tailscale** — Mesh network for secure access to all your nodes\n- 🥒 **Big Pickel x5** — 5 OpenCode Zen API accounts as fallback providers:\n  - `big-pickel1/big-pickle` — Account #1\n  - `big-pickel2/big-pickle` — Account #2\n  - `big-pickel3/big-pickle` — Account #3\n  - `big-pickel4/big-pickle` — Account #4\n  - `big-pickel5/big-pickle` — Account #5\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Quick Reference\n\n### On a fresh Codespace (first time ever)\n\n```bash\n# 1. Clone\ngit clone https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\ncd Codespace-3\n\n# 2. Run full setup\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh\n\n# 3. Start everything\n./start.sh\n\n# 4. Expose ports in Codespaces Ports panel:\n#    - 18789 → OpenClaw Dashboard\n#    - 20128 → 9-router API\n```\n\n### Restarting the same Codespace (stopped & resumed)\n\n```bash\ncd Codespace-3\n./start.sh\n```\n\nThat's it. `start.sh` handles all three services:\n1. 🔗 Tailscale — starts daemon, authenticates with auth key, enables SSH\n2. 🌐 9-router — starts on port 20128\n3. 🤖 OpenClaw — starts Gateway on port 18789\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Services Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Your Codespace                      │\n│                                                         │\n│   ┌────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────┐  │\n│   │    OpenClaw (L4)   │   │      9-router           │  │\n│   │    :18789          │◄──►│      :20128             │  │\n│   │    Big Pickel fall-│   │   (Big Pickel primary)   │  │\n│   │    backs 1-5       │   │                         │  │\n│   └────────┬───────────┘   └──────────┬──────────────┘  │\n│            │                          │                 │\n│            ▼                          ▼                 │\n│   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n│   │                 Tailscale                      │     │\n│   │    (mesh network, SSH enabled, auth key set)   │     │\n│   └───────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Ports\n\n| Port | Service | Access |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| **18789** | OpenClaw Dashboard | Codespaces Ports |\n| **20128** | 9-router API (OpenAI-compatible) | localhost or Tailscale |\n\n---\n\n## 📋 All Commands\n\n### Service lifecycle (run from workspace root)\n\n```bash\n./start.sh              # Start all services in order\n```\n\n### Individual services\n\n```bash\n./bin/start-tailscale   # Install + start daemon + authenticate + SSH\n./bin/start-9router     # Start AI model router\n./bin/start-openclaw    # Start OpenClaw Gateway\n```\n\n---\n\n## 📦 What Gets Synced to the Repo\n\nEverything is pushed to the `main` branch of this repo:\n\n- ✅ **OpenClaw config** — All providers (9router + big-pickel 1-5)\n- ✅ **Workspace files** — AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, MEMORY.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, IDENTITY.md\n- ✅ **Setup & start scripts** — `setup.sh`, `start.sh`, `bin/*`\n- ✅ **Session continuity** — Conversations persist across codespace restarts\n\n---\n\n## 🔄 Rolling Over to a New Codespace\n\nWhen you eventually move to a new Codespace:\n\n1. **On the old codespace:** Push any pending changes:\n   ```bash\n   cd Codespace-3\n   git add -A && git commit -m \"pre-move snapshot\" && git push origin main\n   ```\n\n2. **On the new codespace:**\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\n   cd Codespace-3\n   chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh   # Full setup\n   ./start.sh                         # Start everything\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 🔧 Troubleshooting\n\n| Symptom | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Can't reach OpenClaw | Expose **port 18789** in Codespaces Ports panel |\n| 9-router offline | Check: `curl http://127.0.0.1:20128/v1/models` |\n| Tailscale won't connect | Run `./bin/start-tailscale` manually |\n| Need to switch Big Pickel provider | Change `model.primary` in Control UI or config |\n| `openclaw: command not found` | Run `npm install -g openclaw` |\n| Session lost after restart | Should persist — Gateway saves to disk |\n\n---\n\n## 🔒 Security Notes\n\n- This is a **private repository** (you're the only user)\n- All API keys and auth tokens are stored in open config files intentionally\n- Tailscale encrypts all traffic end-to-end\n- CDP/DevTools ports should stay localhost-only\n\n---\n\n## 🗺️ Roadmap (Coming Soon)\n\n- 🖥️ Remote Browser (Docker Chrome)\n- 💰 Money Printer\n- 📝 Auto-sync cron jobs\n","path":"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/README.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"content\": \"# 🐾 L4 Claw Pack — Portable AI Environment\\n\\n> Your entire AI environment: OpenClaw agent, 9-router, Tailscale, and 5x Big Pickel fallback providers.\\n> **Codespaces are temporary. The `main` branch is your home.**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🏠 What This Is\\n\\nA self-contained AI agent workspace that runs on GitHub Codespaces. Everything you need to run L4 (Leon AI 4) with multiple Big Pickel model fallbacks from [opencode.ai](https://opencode.ai).\\n\\n### What's inside:\\n\\n- 🤖 **OpenClaw** — Your AI agent (L4), with memory, conversations, and identity\\n- 🌐 **9-router** — AI model router (port 20128), currently routing to Big Pickel\\n- 🔗 **Tailscale** — Mesh network for secure access to all your nodes\\n- 🥒 **Big Pickel x5** — 5 OpenCode Zen API accounts as fallback providers:\\n  - `big-pickel1/big-pickle` — Account #1\\n  - `big-pickel2/big-pickle` — Account #2\\n  - `big-pickel3/big-pickle` — Account #3\\n  - `big-pickel4/big-pickle` — Account #4\\n  - `big-pickel5/big-pickle` — Account #5\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🚀 Quick Reference\\n\\n### On a fresh Codespace (first time ever)\\n\\n```bash\\n# 1. Clone\\ngit clone https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\\ncd Codespace-3\\n\\n# 2. Run full setup\\nchmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh\\n\\n# 3. Start everything\\n./start.sh\\n\\n# 4. Expose ports in Codespaces Ports panel:\\n#    - 18789 → OpenClaw Dashboard\\n#    - 20128 → 9-router API\\n```\\n\\n### Restarting the same Codespace (stopped & resumed)\\n\\n```bash\\ncd Codespace-3\\n./start.sh\\n```\\n\\nThat's it. `start.sh` handles all three services:\\n1. 🔗 Tailscale — starts daemon, authenticates with auth key, enables SSH\\n2. 🌐 9-router — starts on port 20128\\n3. 🤖 OpenClaw — starts Gateway on port 18789\\n\\n---\\n\\n## ⚡ Services Overview\\n\\n```\\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n│                     Your Codespace                      │\\n│                                                         │\\n│   ┌────────────────────┐   ┌─────────────────────────┐  │\\n│   │    OpenClaw (L4)   │   │      9-router           │  │\\n│   │    :18789          │◄──►│      :20128             │  │\\n│   │    Big Pickel fall-│   │   (Big Pickel primary)   │  │\\n│   │    backs 1-5       │   │                         │  │\\n│   └────────┬───────────┘   └──────────┬──────────────┘  │\\n│            │                          │                 │\\n│            ▼                          ▼                 │\\n│   ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────┐     │\\n│   │                 Tailscale                      │     │\\n│   │    (mesh network, SSH enabled, auth key set)   │     │\\n│   └───────────────────────────────────────────────┘     │\\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n### Ports\\n\\n| Port | Service | Access |\\n|------|---------|--------|\\n| **18789** | OpenClaw Dashboard | Codespaces Ports |\\n| **20128** | 9-router API (OpenAI-compatible) | localhost or Tailscale |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📋 All Commands\\n\\n### Service lifecycle (run from workspace root)\\n\\n```bash\\n./start.sh              # Start all services in order\\n```\\n\\n### Individual services\\n\\n```bash\\n./bin/start-tailscale   # Install + start daemon + authenticate + SSH\\n./bin/start-9router     # Start AI model router\\n./bin/start-openclaw    # Start OpenClaw Gateway\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 📦 What Gets Synced to the Repo\\n\\nEverything is pushed to the `main` branch of this repo:\\n\\n- ✅ **OpenClaw config** — All providers (9router + big-pickel 1-5)\\n- ✅ **Workspace files** — AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, MEMORY.md, USER.md, TOOLS.md, IDENTITY.md\\n- ✅ **Setup & start scripts** — `setup.sh`, `start.sh`, `bin/*`\\n- ✅ **Session continuity** — Conversations persist across codespace restarts\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔄 Rolling Over to a New Codespace\\n\\nWhen you eventually move to a new Codespace:\\n\\n1. **On the old codespace:** Push any pending changes:\\n   ```bash\\n   cd Codespace-3\\n   git add -A && git commit -m \\\"pre-move snapshot\\\" && git push origin main\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **On the new codespace:**\\n   ```bash\\n   git clone https://github.com/Walusimbi-Leon1/Codespace-3.git\\n   cd Codespace-3\\n   chmod +x setup.sh && ./setup.sh   # Full setup\\n   ./start.sh                         # Start everything\\n   ```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔧 Troubleshooting\\n\\n| Symptom | Fix |\\n|---------|-----|\\n| Can't reach OpenClaw | Expose **port 18789** in Codespaces Ports panel |\\n| 9-router offline | Check: `curl http://127.0.0.1:20128/v1/models` |\\n| Tailscale won't connect | Run `./bin/start-tailscale` manually |\\n| Need to switch Big Pickel provider | Change `model.primary` in Control UI or config |\\n| `openclaw: command not found` | Run `npm install -g openclaw` |\\n| Session lost after restart | Should persist — Gateway saves to disk |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🔒 Security Notes\\n\\n- This is a **private repository** (you're the only user)\\n- All API keys and auth tokens are stored in open config files intentionally\\n- Tailscale encrypts all traffic end-to-end\\n- CDP/DevTools ports should stay localhost-only\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 🗺️ Roadmap (Coming Soon)\\n\\n- 🖥️ Remote Browser (Docker Chrome)\\n- 💰 Money Printer\\n- 📝 Auto-sync cron jobs\\n\", \"path\": \"/home/codespace/.openclaw/workspace/README.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"9router","model":"oc/big-pickle","usage":{"input":2048,"output":1734,"cacheRead":72832,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":210,"totalTokens":76614,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782316181315,"responseId":"c36aea5c-1531-4dd3-b6f3-86e47f9c922f"}}
